.Dd January 31, 2005
.Dt JAIL_ATTACH 2
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm jail_attach
.Nd attach current process to an existing jail
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libc
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/types.h
.In sys/jail.h
.Ft int
.Fn jail_attach "int id"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
system call attaches the current process to an existing jail referenced by
.Nm id .
.Pp
The argument is an int referencing the ID of the prison.
.Sh ERRORS
.Fn jail_attach
will fail if:
.Bl -tag -width Er
.It Bq Er EPERM
The user is not the super user, or is already in a prison.
.It Bq Er EINVAL
The prison referenced by
.Nm id
does not exist.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr chroot 2 ,
.Xr jail 2 ,
.Xr jail 8 ,
.Xr jexec 8 ,
.Xr jls 8
.Sh HISTORY
